{"title_page": "Chikuzen-Fukae Station", "text_new": "{{short description|Railway station in Itoshima, Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Chikuzen-Fukae Station\n| native_name = \u7b51\u524d\u6df1\u6c5f\u99c5\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| type        = \n| image       = Chikuzen-Fukae Station 20161101-2.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| other_name  = \n| address     = [[Itoshima, Fukuoka|Itoshima]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka]]\n| country     = Japan\n| coordinates = {{coord|33|30|54.5|N|130|8|21|E|type:railwaystation_region:JP|display=inline,title}}\n| operator    = [[Kyushu Railway Company|JR Kyushu]]\n| line        = [[Chikuhi Line]]\n| platforms   =  \n| connections = \n| structure   = \n| code        = \n| opened      = 1924\n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = \n| pass_year   = \n| services    = \n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Chikuzen-Fukae Station'''|\u7b51\u524d\u6df1\u6c5f\u99c5|Chikuzen-Fukae-eki}} is a train station in Nij\u014d-Fukae, [[Itoshima, Fukuoka|Itoshima]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is operated by [[Kyushu Railway Company]] (JR Kyushu).\n\nThis station is where through-service trains from the [[Fukuoka City Subway]] [[K\u016bk\u014d Line (Fukuoka City Subway)|K\u016bk\u014d Line]] (Airport Line) normally terminate.\n\n==Lines==\n*[[Kyushu Railway Company|JR Kyushu]]\n**[[Chikuhi Line]]\n\n==Layout==\nChikuzen-Fukae Station is a ground level station with one [[island platform]] serving two tracks.\n\n== Adjacent stations ==\n{{service rail start}}\n{{j-route|route=Chikuhi Line|col=red}}\n{{j-rserv|previous={{STN|Ikisan}}|next={{STN|Dainy\u016b}}|service=Local}}\n{{j-rserv|previous={{STN|Chikuzen-Maebaru}}|next={{STN|Hamasaki}}|service=Rapid Service}}\n{{end box}}\n\n==Environs==\n*[[Route 202 (Japan)|National Route 202]]\n*Itoshima City Office Nij\u014d Branch\n\n==History==\n*April 1, 1924 - Station is established by Kitakyushu Railroad.\n*October 1, 1937 - The Railroad Ministry nationalizes all railroads, this station becomes a station of the [[Chikuhi Line]].\n*April 1, 1987 - Railways privatize and [[Kyushu Railway Company|JR Kyushu]] inherits this station.\n*March 23, 2002 - The driving area of the Fukuoka City Subway vehicle extended to this station.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/EkiApp?LISTID=502&EKI=91118140 Chikuzen-Fukae Station (JR Kyushu)] {{in lang|ja}}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Chikuhi Line}}\n\n{{Fukuoka-railstation-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1924]]\n[[Category:Chikuhi Line]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Fukuoka Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Stations of Kyushu Railway Company]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Railway station in Itoshima, Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Chikuzen-Fukae Station\n| native_name = \u7b51\u524d\u6df1\u6c5f\u99c5\n| native_name_lang = ja\n| type        = \n| image       = Chikuzen-Fukae Station 20161101-2.jpg\n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| other_name  = \n| address     = [[Itoshima, Fukuoka|Itoshima]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka]]\n| country     = Japan\n| coordinates = {{coord|33|30|54.5|N|130|8|21|E|type:railwaystation_region:JP|display=inline,title}}\n| operator    = [[Kyushu Railway Company|JR Kyushu]]\n| line        = [[Chikuhi Line]]\n| platforms   =  \n| connections = \n| structure   = \n| code        = \n| opened      = 1924\n| closed      = \n| former      =  \n| passengers  = \n| pass_year   = \n| services    = \n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Chikuzen-Fukae Station'''|\u7b51\u524d\u6df1\u6c5f\u99c5|Chikuzen-Fukae-eki}} is a train station in Nij\u014d-Fukae, [[Itoshima, Fukuoka|Itoshima City]], [[Fukuoka Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is operated by [[Kyushu Railway Company]] (JR Kyushu).\n\nThis station is where through-service trains from the [[Fukuoka City Subway]] [[K\u016bk\u014d Line (Fukuoka City Subway)|K\u016bk\u014d Line]] (Airport Line) normally terminate.\n\n==Lines==\n*[[Kyushu Railway Company|JR Kyushu]]\n**[[Chikuhi Line]]\n\n==Layout==\nChikuzen-Fukae Station is a ground level station with one [[island platform]] serving two tracks.\n\n== Adjacent stations ==\n{{service rail start}}\n{{j-route|route=Chikuhi Line|col=red}}\n{{j-rserv|previous={{STN|Ikisan}}|next={{STN|Dainy\u016b}}|service=Local}}\n{{j-rserv|previous={{STN|Chikuzen-Maebaru}}|next={{STN|Hamasaki}}|service=Rapid Service}}\n{{end box}}\n\n==Environs==\n*[[Route 202 (Japan)|National Route 202]]\n*Itoshima City Office Nij\u014d Branch\n\n==History==\n*April 1, 1924 - Station is established by Kitakyushu Railroad.\n*October 1, 1937 - The Railroad Ministry nationalizes all railroads, this station becomes a station of the [[Chikuhi Line]].\n*April 1, 1987 - Railways privatize and [[Kyushu Railway Company|JR Kyushu]] inherits this station.\n*March 23, 2002 - The driving area of the Fukuoka City Subway vehicle extended to this station.\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.jrkyushu.co.jp/EkiApp?LISTID=502&EKI=91118140 Chikuzen-Fukae Station (JR Kyushu)] {{in lang|ja}}\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Chikuhi Line}}\n\n{{Fukuoka-railstation-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1924]]\n[[Category:Chikuhi Line]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Fukuoka Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Stations of Kyushu Railway Company]]\n", "name_user": "Ganbaruby", "label": "safe", "comment": "MOS:JPPLACE", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chikuzen-Fukae_Station"}
